%pyspark
from pyspark.ml.linalg import Vectors
from pyspark.sql import Row

appointments = spark.table("appointments")
data =  appointments.select("Age", "Sick").withColumn("Sick", appointments["Sick"])

data = data.rdd.map(lambda r: Row(label=int(r[1]), features=Vectors.dense(r[0]))).toDF()
data.show()

%pyspark
# Import LinearRegression class
from pyspark.ml.regression import LinearRegression

# Define LinearRegression algorithm
lr = LinearRegression().setLabelCol("label").setFeaturesCol("features")

# Fit 2 models, using different regularization parameters
modelA = lr.fit(data, {lr.regParam:0.0})
modelB = lr.fit(data, {lr.regParam:100.0})

%pyspark
from pyspark.ml.evaluation import RegressionEvaluator
evaluator = RegressionEvaluator(metricName="rmse")
RMSE = evaluator.evaluate(predictionsA)
print("ModelA: Root Mean Squared Error = " + str(RMSE))

%pyspark
predictionsB = modelB.transform(data)
RMSE = evaluator.evaluate(predictionsB)
print("ModelB: Root Mean Squared Error = " + str(RMSE))
